  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0baf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc8\u00a0 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd - \u0ba4\u0bc7\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0baa\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "People will completely ignore the use of private bus services - National Transport Commission",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "No firm decision has been taken on the bus fare hike due to disagreement between the private bus associations on what percentage increase in bus fare should be in line with fuel prices.",
        "Nilan Mirunda, chairman of the National Transport Commission, said that if the bus fare hike was in line with the demands of the private bus associations, the public would completely ignore the use of the private bus service.",
        "He mentioned that it has been decided to carry out negotiations with the Ministry of Power and the Ministry of Finance regarding the request of the association to distribute fuel to the private bus service at relief price without increasing the bus fare in the interest of the public passengers.",
        "The All Ceylon Private Bus Operators Association has demanded a 30 per cent increase in bus fares due to the increase in fuel prices.",
        "Due to lack of consensus among the private bus owners association regarding the bus fare revision, no firm final decision on the fare hike was taken.",
        "The Minister of Transport has expressed dissatisfaction with the union's demand for a minimum bus fare of 40 rupees.",
        "In the current crisis situation, we need to be vigilant about increasing bus fares.",
        "Transport Minister Bandula Gunawardena said during talks with the unions that he had decided to negotiate with the Ministry of Energy and Finance to provide fuel for private buses on a relief basis without increasing bus fares.",
        "He said a firm decision on the bus fare revision would be announced in a couple of days."
      ],
